sentences: Founding members Hannah Van Loon (vocals, guitar and keyboard) and Emma Oppen (vocals and bass) left the band in 2016.
The members of Trails and Ways met while attending UC Berkeley, and the band was formed in early 2012, after members had lived abroad in Brazil and Spain.
For example, their song "Skeletons" is about dancing at a club, then being "fast-forwarded a thousand years to what was left of the club on an ecologically collapsed earth".
In 2015, they signed on with Barsuk Records.
